        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:16PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 13 miles east of Nashoba to
8 miles east of Cloudy. Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Battiest, Pickens, and Bethel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
